ce of the traumatic political and historical changes they were living through.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aGermansxIntellectual lifexCaliforniaxLos Angeles. 0aGermanszCaliforniazLos AngelesxIntellectual life. 0aJews, GermanxIntellectual lifexCaliforniaxLos AngelesxCaliforniaxLos Angeles. 0aJews, GermanzCaliforniazLos AngelesxIntellectual life. 0aModernism (Aesthetics)xCaliforniaxLos Angeles. 0aModernism (Aesthetics)zCaliforniazLos Angeles. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / West (AK, CA, CO, HI, ID, MT, NV, UT, WY).2bisacsh  a18th century.  a1930s.  a1940s.  a20th century.  aamerican history.  aarnold schoenberg.  abertolt brecht.  acalifornia.  aclassicism.  aehrhard bahr.  aexile.  afritz lang.  agerman artists.  agerman modernism.  agermany.  aintellectual.  alos angeles.  amodernism.  anational socialism.  apacific coast.  aschoenberg.  asocialism.  asouthern california.  atheodore adorno.  athomas mann.  aunited states history.  aus history.  aweimer germany.  aweimer republic.  awest coast.  awestern united states.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093380440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520933804423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520933804/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles